Quote: ... lastly, record of early connection with South Africa, with the Cape of Good Hope, is preserved by such plant-names as `Capeweed' (<i>Crepis taraxacifolia</i>), `Cape gooseberry' (<i>Physalis peruviana</i>), and `Cape barley', not improbably from its hardihood, the old Scottish bere (<i>Hordeum</i> sp.).
